fields.text: Any fool can write code that a computer can understand. Good programmers write code that humans can understand.
fields.author: Martin Fowler

fields.text: The only way to learn a new programming language is by writing programs in it.
fields.author: Dennis Ritchie

fields.text: First, solve the problem. Then, write the code.
fields.author: John Johnson

fields.text: Measuring programming progress by lines of code is like measuring aircraft building progress by weight.
fields.author: Bill Gates

fields.text: Programs must be written for people to read, and only incidentally for machines to execute.
fields.author: Harold Abelson

fields.text: There are only two hard things in computer science: cache invalidation and naming things.
fields.author: Phil Karlton

fields.text: The computer was born to solve problems that did not exist before.
fields.author: Bill Gates

fields.text: The best way to predict the future is to invent it.
fields.author: Alan Kay

fields.text: If debugging is the process of removing software bugs, then programming must be the process of putting them in.
fields.author: Edsger Dijkstra

fields.text: Walking on water and developing software from a specification are easy if both are frozen.
fields.author: Edward V Berard
